Phone: Phone (33) 76 51 48 78  
Abstract: In this paper we describe a system for detection and correction of lexical and syntactic errors in a French text. The lexical level uses several techniques (keys, phonetics and morphological generation). The aim of the syntactic level is verification of the structure of a sentence and of relations between words (e.g. agreement). It proceeds by unification of the decorations on the nodes of a dependency tree, by application of condition-action rules. By use of a morphological generator, corrections can be offered for agreement errors. We propose to integrate the two levels in a complete tool, based on a real size lexicon. 
